description: For sale: $274,900. Welcome to your own private oasis of 400 feet of lake shore plus 8 acres on beautiful Vanduse Lake. So much to offer with this 4 bedroom, 2 bath walkout rambler! The big ole barn plus the huge 44 x 88 pole building are just waiting for you and your ideas. New metal roof on the house and a newer well (2017). House could easily be split into a duplex. Come check this out! Heaven awaits.

For sale: $249,900. Built in 2007, this private home sits on 80 mixed acres and is served by an artesion well.  Just minutes to Jacobson, the township plows and maintains the main 660th Lane.  Lots of wildlife with trails and deer stands, open and wooded, with backwater wetland from the Mississippi. Includes attached garage as well as pole building with shop and newer garden shed. Open floor plan has kitchen/dining area and adjacent family room has Yodel wood stove, which serves as secondary heat for the home. Many quality features including cement board siding and top of the line boiler system. Excellent location in between Duluth, Twin Cities and Grand Rapids.

For sale: $449,000. Have your own Private Lake Home, set on 40 acres, with hundreds of state land to access. Beautiful, log sided home on Lost Lake, 2 miles north of Big Sandy.  A must see!  An amazing home with 3 bedroom, 3 bath. Open kitchen and dining room, vaulted living room with a cozy fireplace, and picturesque views of the lake from all rooms. Large lower level family room with walk out basement to the lake.  Well groomed yard, gorgeous pines, poplar and maple trees.  Enjoy many good times with family or friends catching fish of all kinds.Then go for walk to simply enjoy nature's beauty on hundreds of state forest lands, or hunt deer, grouse, and bear. Barbecue on the huge wrap around deck. Roast marshmallows in the fire pit for fun. Everything an outdoor lover could want right outside your door! Property has many out buildings for your boat & toys, 22x28 detached garage, 30x28 steel shed, 3 story, 41x32 red barn, 21x31 storage shed, 18x24 log sided guest house. Breathtaking sunsets.

description: Recently sold: $215,000. Fantastic architecturally designed home on the Mississippi River.  Situated on over 11 acres of property, this home was designed with a specific feel in mind.  The kitchen is fantastic with custom black ash cabinets, and flooring, pantry, and stainless steel appliances including a six burner stove and convection oven, tin ceiling and gorgeous countertops.  Large living room with custom black ash flooring and trim work.  Upper level features a huge master bedroom with an additional space that would make a spectacular office, complete with vaulted ceilings, a full bath and closet. Main level and upper level river side deck offer a serene place to relax.  The detached two stall garage allows you space for toys and vehicles.  The adorable outdoor sauna is perfect to enjoy on those cooler summer evenings!  Do not delay, this is a wonderful opportunity to experience the peace and privacy the great "up north" has to offer. *** Call Me Today For a Showing --- 218-259-5068***
